resources.string: Hello, this is AISEC VIt chapter. We do a lot of work related to a lot of people and we go to places and hangout all over the world

AIESEC is the world’s largest youth run organization which has been activating potential for 69 years and has approximately 70,000 members in 126 countries and territories and has delivered over 480,000 experiences to date. \n\n We are a non-governmental not-for- profit organization that has been endorsed by the United Nations, multiple presidents world-wide, CEOs of multinational corporations and recognised by UNESCO.

Our vision and motto is “We strive to achieve peace and fulfilment of humankind’s potential.” by providing the youth a platform to develop their leadership skills and promoting cross-cultural global exchanges with a focus of creating a positive impact on society. \n\n We believe that it is every young person’s responsibility to take a positive role shaping the future of our planet and everyone deserves the chance, and tools, to fulfil their potential. We provide young people with self-driven, practical, global experiences. We empower them to see the world, have a genuine effect and find what really matters to them.

Global Volunteer is an intensive international volunteer abroad experience that enables you to work on projects that impact social issues. Through this we empower communities by developing the people and enabling them to develop a more sustainable and healthy future. Overall, through this program, AIESEC is providing young students an opportunity to develop entrepreneurial and leadership skills through international internships mainly on social issues which will help them enrich their education, challenge their worldview and help them gain a unique combination of multi cultural, social and entrepreneurial experience during the formative years of their lives. We have a wide range of more than 20 countries with Global Volunteering projects in store.

Outgoing Global Entrepreneur provides a platform for enabling transformation through an entrepreneurial experience in start up environments abroad. The duration of the experience ranges from 6 weeks until 12 weeks. Depending on the project accepted for, a stipend may or may not be provided. Are you ready to venture into the world full of opportunities unexplored? In the race to be better than the best, we need to do things even best can not imagine. Taking the road less travelled is not just a myth anymore. Technical internships abroad is the way forward to stand out. Outgoing Global Talent allows you to work for 3 to 18 months in a corporate environment with regards to various fields of interests with a regulated stipend depending on the project accepted for. With flexible timelines and a world full of possibilities what are you waiting for?

It is a big beautiful world, isn\'t it? What limits our understanding of this world are stereotypes and how we form opinions without seeing things for ourselves. AIESEC demands to change this, we believe in our youth to be fair. Incoming Exchange, is the department that ensures people from across oceans have a chance to stay with us, to help us grow while we help them grow.
